JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng government has blamed a contractor for the roof collapse at the Charlotte Maxeke Academic Hospital on Thursday.The province's infrastructure development MEC Jacob Mamabolo said the contractors, tasked with fixing the roof, were immediately removed from the site.READ: Part of Charlotte Maxeke Hospital's roof collapses"It is very clear, the manner in which they approached the work, it is certain that they could have taken measures to make sure that what we are sitting with did not happen," Mamabolo told journalists.Terrified patients and staff at the Johannesburg hospital fled the building when a roof partially collapsed.The incident happened in a busy area near the maternity ward. Five people were injured.eNCA